### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
what are the verb tenses?

### Response:


Verb Tense refers to the time frame in which a verb takes place. There are three main types of verb tenses: past, present and future. Each type has four forms: simple (base form), continuous (with -ing ending), perfect (has/had + base form) and perfect continuous (has/had + been + base form).
